---
description: Embod authoring conventions for project files and AI-generated example models.
globs:
  - "**/embod_project.py"
  - "examples/**/*.py"
  - "tests/fixtures/ai_cases/**/*.py"
---

When editing Embod model files:

- prefer `Project`, `Part`, `Assembly`, `Robot`, `Link`, `Joint`, `Frame`,
  `InterfaceDef`, `PrintProfile`, and `CollisionDef`
- keep manufacturable parts separate from robot semantics
- use explicit names for `parts`, `assemblies`, `links`, and `joints`
- add `PrintProfile` for printable parts whenever practical
- add `CollisionDef` and `mass_kg` for robot links
- preserve the validation loop: buildable geometry, explicit exports, and
  snapshot-friendly structure

If the request is underspecified, ask for measurements before changing the file.
